OL,4,Ccouncil leader in history
OL,6,FAsked by opposition councillor Wendy
OL,7,FTaylor if members of the Labour
OL,8,Fcabinet would speak candidly if
OL,9,Fquestioned over "their awareness of
OL,10,Finappropriate behaviour", the new
OL,11,Fcouncil leader replied that "honesty
OL,12,Fcan always be expected" but that the
OL,13,Fongoing complaint process "should be
OL,14,Fallowed to be completed without
OL,15,Fpolitical interference or commentary".
