OL,3,CNewcastle appoints first female
OL,4,Ccouncil leader in history
OL,6,FThe Local Democracy Reporting Service
OL,7,Frevealed last Friday that she was
OL,8,Fpoised to take over as council leader,
OL,9,Fhaving emerged as the sole candidate
OL,10,Fto replace Cllr Kemp in a party
OL,11,Fleadership election.
OL,13,FWhile the national Labour Party had
OL,14,Fintervened in the contest last week
OL,15,Fand other potential candidates are
OL,16,Funderstood to have been asked to come
OL,17,Fforward, Cllr Kilgour remained the
OL,18,Fonly name on the shortlist that was
OL,19,Fpresented to the city's Labour
OL,20,Fcouncillors at a meeting to choose
OL,21,Ftheir new group leader on Monday night.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/13
